  <section class="recipe" id="meatballs">
    <h2>Homemade Meatballs with Onion and Chili</h2>
    <p>Juicy homemade meatballs made with finely chopped onion, salt, black pepper, and a little kick of chili.</p>

    <h3>Ingredients (serves 4)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>600 g ground beef</li>
      <li>1 yellow onion (about 120 g), finely chopped</li>
      <li>1 red chili (about 10–15 g), finely chopped</li>
      <li>10 g salt</li>
      <li>3 g black pepper (about 1 tsp)</li>
      <li>30 ml water</li>
      <li>20 ml neutral cooking oil (for frying)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Instructions</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Add the ground beef to a mixing bowl.</li>
      <li>Add chopped onion, chili, salt, black pepper, and water.</li>
      <li>Mix well for 2–3 minutes until the mixture becomes smooth and slightly sticky.</li>
      <li>Shape into meatballs using slightly wet hands (about 5–6 cm).</li>
      <li>Heat a frying pan over medium-high heat and add oil.</li>
      <li>Fry 3–4 minutes per side until nicely browned.</li>
      <li>Lower heat and cook 4–6 minutes until fully cooked.</li>
      <li>Rest for 2 minutes before serving.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Tips</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>For a milder flavor: use half the chili or remove the seeds.</li>
      <li>For extra juicy meatballs: add more water (up to 50 ml) and mix longer.</li>
      <li>If making larger meatballs: cook longer on lower heat.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Required Equipment</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Mixing bowl</li>
      <li>Cutting board and knife</li>
      <li>Frying pan</li>
      <li>Spatula</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Allergen Information</h3>
    <p>No known allergens in the basic recipe. Check any sides for allergens.</p>

    <a class="back-to-top" href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
  </section>

